to the editor how quickly the high regard afforded scientists by public officials during the anthrax attacks was eroded after the announcement of advances in human cloning by a biotech company bush denounces cloning and calls for ban news article nov 27 assurances that the goal of the experiments was the production of therapeutic stem cells seemed to be ignored and the leap was made to a grossly oversimplified discussion of the morality of creating life i was impressed in recent weeks by the positive public interplay between government officials the press and working scientists an uncommonly positive image for youngsters thinking about their future it would be a shame to lose a valuable growing dialogue because the issues are more subtle and have political implications regina linder new york nov 27 2001 the writer is director of the medical laboratory sciences program hunter college cuny

